 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Convergence Engine — Materialized F(S) + Gradient Routing + Session Daemon (INV-BILATERAL-001 L1, INV-GUIDANCE-010, INV-COHERENCE-004, ADR-STORE-019). BACKGROUND: The spec formalizes DDIS as a convergent dynamical system: F(S) is monotonically non-decreasing (L1 law), R(t) follows steepest descent on the fitness landscape (INV-GUIDANCE-010), and geodesic pursuit converges in bounded steps (INV-COHERENCE-004). Current implementation computes F(S) in batch (29s at 37K datoms) and uses graph-metric proxies for gradient. This EPIC implements the spec correctly: F(S) as incremental materialized view (O(1) read, O(k) update), gradient routing via project_delta (exact 7-dimensional delta-F(S)), and session daemon for I/O elimination + W_alpha + CRDT sync. Three phases: Phase 0 (MaterializedViews in Store kernel — solves 97% of perf), Phase 1 (Gradient routing — makes system self-steering), Phase 2 (Session daemon — eliminates remaining I/O). Each phase independently valuable. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid status < 2s in embedded mode (Phase 0). (B) R(t) routing uses exact gradient, not graph-metric proxy (Phase 1). (C) braid status < 100ms with daemon (Phase 2). (D) All 1595+ existing tests pass. (E) F(S) materialized views match batch compute_fitness to within epsilon. (F) Multi-agent gradient coordination demonstrated (two agents, shared store, no explicit communication). TRACES-TO: INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-GUIDANCE-010, INV-COHERENCE-004, INV-STORE-013, ADR-STORE-019."
